Spring MVC:

1.if we develop a webapplication according to the mvc architecture manually, we need to develop
 Servlet class, jsp file and all the flow control logic manually.

2.Spring f/w provides Spring-web-mvc module to simplify the manual mvc application development
in which , Spring mvc module provides a predefined Servlet class with predefined flow control
 logic , ie. DispatcherServlet class.

Spring Boot:

1.It is a spring platform that mainly focus on convenstion over configuration.

2.It is not a f/w s/w, it is just a spring application development platform which 
provides RAD(Rapid Application development) feature to the Spring f/w.

3.Spring boot support auto-configuration.

4.It provides integrated tomcat server, so we can develop webapplication/webservices without 
installing WebServer.

5.with the help of Spring boot, we can develop WA, WS, microservices , Spring cloud based 
application very easily.
